I"$<p>Featuring Nadia Abu El-Haj on <em>Combat Trauma: Imaginaries of War and Citizenship in Post-9/11 America</em>. How the civil-military divide makes troops into super citizens and what it means that agents of state violence are turning to the grammar of identity politics—and more. The second in a two-part interview.</p>

